<div class="preview-card">
  <p class="preview-card__eyebrow">What We Reject</p>
  <h3 class="preview-card__title">Semitexa SSR is explicitly designed against rendering drift and framework dependency drift.</h3>
  <p class="preview-card__summary">
    These are not random implementation details. They are the specific splits Semitexa tries to prevent before they
    turn an SSR app into a pile of “just one more client-side exception” and “just one more required frontend library”.
  </p>

  <div class="preview-table">
    <table>
      <thead>
        <tr>
          <th>Common drift</th>
          <th>Semitexa answer</th>
        </tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        {% for item in mapping %}
          <tr>
            <td>{{ item.anti }}</td>
            <td>{{ item.answer }}</td>
          </tr>
        {% endfor %}
      </tbody>
    </table>
  </div>
</div>
